Afripalm Signs Deal to Build S.African Steel Mill, Bus. Day Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-02-23T05:05:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/afripalm-signs-deal-to-build-s-african-steel-mill-bus-day-says.html
Afripalm Resources has signed a
memorandum of understanding with  Steel Authority of India Ltd .
to build a 21 billion rand ($2.9 billion) steel mill in  South
Africa , Business Day said, citing Afripalm Chairman Lazarus Zim.  The mill, which will compete with  ArcelorMittal  South
Africa Ltd., aims to produce between 3 million metric tons and 5
million tons of steel a year, the Johannesburg-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  